ERC International Inc. said it entered into new three-year revolving loan agreements totaling $25 million. 

ERC said the lines of credit with American Security Bank of Washington, D.C., and Sovran Bank of Richmond, Va., are unsecured and interest rates are at or below the prime rate.
The engineering services company said it planned to use the credit lines for general corporate purposes. 

Sovran Bank is a unit of Sovran Financial Corp., Norfolk, Va., while American Security is a unit of Baltimore-based MNC Financial Inc. 

